habitat: Limestone cliffs above intermittent creek above inundation zone; guajillo-Vasey oak-Plateau liveoak-poreleaf-Lindheimer rockdaisy open cliff sparse vegetation. With Acacia berlandieri, Quercus pungens var. vaseyana, Q. fusiformis, Porophyllum scoparium, and Perityle lindheimeri. Infrequent vine.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Satan Canyon. Sample plot no. 7. Satan Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone) alluvium along intermittent creek in former inundation zone; Roosevelt weed-creek indigo sparse shrubland with white boneset, Bermuda grass, King Ranch bluestem, annual spikesedge, and Gulf Coast spikesedge. With Baccharis neglecta, Eupatorium serotinum, Porophyllum scoparium, Acacia minuata, Indigofera lindheimeri, Eleocharis cellulosa, E. geniculata, Cynodon dactylon, and Bothriochloa ischaemum var. songarica. Rare annual to 15 cm. Corolla pale blue.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Satan Canyon. Sample plot no. 7. Satan Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

locality: Near TPWD bunkhouse above E bank of Devils River between mouths of Satan and Little Satan canyons, ca. 9 airmiles NW of jct. US Rt. 277 and road to Rough Canyon Recreation Area. SW part Devils River State Natural Area Southern Unit.

habitat: Steep, rocky (limestone), west-facing slope just below retaining wall in parking area; guajillo shrubland with evergreen sumac and buffelgrass. With Rhus virens, Acacia berlandieri, and Cenchrus ciliaris. Rare shrub to 1 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone and asphalt) soils at base of west-facing roadcut in limestone cliff; blackbrush shrubland with buffelgrass and parralena. With Acacia rigidula, Cenchrus ciliaris, and Thymophylla pentachaeta. Rare perennial to 75 cm. Corolla light purple.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone and asphalt) soils at base of west-facing roadcut in limestone cliff; blackbrush shrubland with buffelgrass and parralena. With Acacia rigidula, Cenchrus ciliaris, and Thymophylla pentachaeta. Infrequent perennial to 25 cm. Petals white.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Climbing on mesquite and bare ground along gravelly (limestone) disturbed slope; mesquite woodland. With Prosopis glandulosa. Infrequent vine. Corolla yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly disturbed area along road; highly disturbed Roosevelt weed shrubland with buffelgrass, tree tobacco and buttonbush. With Cenchrus ciliaris, Baccharis glutinosa, Nicotiana glauca, and Cephalanthus occidentalis. Infrequent perennial to 1.5 m. Rays white, discs yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Limestone cliff bases; guajillo shrubland with Gregg's ash and brush myrtlecroton. Infrequent vine sprawling on Acacia berlandieri, Fraxinus greggii, and Bernardia myricifolia.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Limestone cliff faces, cliff bases, and gravelly disturbed areas along road; guajillo shrubland with Gregg's ash and brush myrtlecroton. With Acacia berlandieri, Fraxinus greggii, and Bernardia myricifolia. Common perennial to 35 cm. Corolla yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Base of limestone cliff along edge of road in former inundation zone; Roosevelt weed shrubland with silver bluestem, salt cedar, tree tobacco, Johnson grass, and frogfruit. With Baccharis neglecta, Nicotiana glauca, Sorghum jalapense, Bothriochloa laguroides, Phyla nodiflora, and Tamarix ramosissima. Rare annual to 2 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Disturbed, rocky (limestone) road edge in former inundation zone; black willow-salt cedar-Roosevelt weed-Bermuda grass woodland with common ragweed. With Salix nigra, Baccharis neglecta, Ambrosia artemisifolia, and Cynodon dactylon. Common perennial to 7 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Disturbed, gravelly (limestone) clay soils at base of massive, west-facing limestone roadcut; mixed grasses and herbs including silver bluestem, Johnson grass, rocky goldaster, and silverleaf nightshade. With Bothriochloa barbinodis, Sorghum jalapense, Heterotheca fulcrata, Solanum elaeagnifolium, and Gaura suffulta. Locally common perennial to 50 cm. Rays and discs yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Disturbed, gravelly (limestone) clay soils at base of massive, west-facing limestone roadcut; mixed grasses and herbs including silver bluestem, Johnson grass, rocky goldaster, and silverleaf nightshade. Corolla greenish yellow to black with black spots in throat.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Pecos River picnic area and boat launch. Sample plot no. 95. Seminole Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Disturbed, gravelly (limestone) clay soils at base of massive, west-facing limestone roadcut; mixed grasses and herbs including silver bluestem, Johnson grass, rocky goldaster, and silverleaf nightshade. locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Hunt Area 1. Sample plot no. 59. California Creek & Amistad Dam Quads (1:24,000).

habitat: Rocky (limestone), east-facing slope in former inundation zone; blackbrush-Roosevelt weed shrubland with chaste tree, Texas kidneywood, and plains lovegrass. With Baccharis neglecta, Acacia rigidula, Vitex agnus-castus, Eysenhardtia texana, and Eragrostis intermedia. Rare tree to 3 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Blackbrush Point. Sample plot no. 49. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly, thin, dark brown, silty soils over fractured limestone bedrock, upper edge of gentle slope just above former inundation zone; blackbrush shrubland with coyotillo, Texas persimmon, purple threeawn, and Lindheimer and Border pricklypears. With Acacia rigidula, Karwinskia humboldtiana, Diospyros texana, Opuntia engelmannia var. lindheimeri, O. atrispina, and Aristida purpurea. Rare shrub to 1 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: East of Blackbrush Point. Sample plot no. 48. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Rocky (limestone) soils on large level limestone ledge in former inundation zone; blackbrush shrubland with King Ranch bluestem. With Bothriochloa ischaemum var. songarica and Acacia rigidula. Infrequent shrub to 2 m. Corolla purple.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: East of Blackbrush Point. Sample plot no. 48. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone and asphalt), silty, north-facing slope in former inundation zone; blackbrush shrubland with Texas persimmon, King Ranch bluestem, and sideoats grama. With Diospyros texana, Bothriochloa ischaemum var. songarica, Acacia rigidula, and Bouteloua curtipendula. Rare vine.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Blackbrush Point boat ramp. Sample plot no. 49. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone) silty bench above small intermittent drainage in former inundation zone; mesquite woodland with purple threeawn, Lindheimer pricklypear, frogfruit, and Texas thistle. With Aristida purpurea var. purpurea, Opuntia engelmannia var. lindheimeri, Prosopis glandulosa, Cirsium texanum, and Phyla nodiflora. Rare perennial to 50 cm. Corolla golden yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Canyon 74 across from Rio Grande Buoy 28. Sample plot no. 74. Box Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone) silty bench above small intermittent drainage in former inundation zone; huisache-mesquite-salt cedar woodland with tasajillo. With Opuntia leptocaulis, Tamarix ramosissima, and Acacia minuata. Common tree to 5 m.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Canyon 74 across from Rio Grande Buoy 28. Sample plot no. 74. Box Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone) silty bench above small intermittent drainage in former inundation zone; huisache-mesquite-salt cedar woodland with tasajillo. With Opuntia leptocaulis, Prosopis glandulosa, Tamarix ramosissima, and Acacia minuata. Rare shrub to 1 m. Corolla yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Canyon 74 across from Rio Grande Buoy 28. Sample plot no. 74. Box Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Gravelly (limestone), silty soil on almost level flat in former inundation zone; frogfruit-Bermuda grass-water hyssop herbaceous vegetation with threadleaf groundsel. With Senecio flaccidus, Cynodon dactylon, Phyla nodiflora, and Bacopa monnieri. Common annual to 1 m. Corolla purple.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Canyon 74 across from Rio Grande Buoy 24. Sample plot no. 74. Box Canyon Quad (1:24,000).

locality: Along bank of Devils River, ca. 1.3-1.5 airmiles SSE of mouth of Little Satan Canyon at Devils River. Gillis Ranch Quadrangle. Devils River State Natural Area Southern Unit.

habitat: Limestone roadcut in former inundation zone; Roosevelt weed shrubland with buffelgrass, frogfruit and old man's beard. With Phyla nodiflora, Clematis drummondii, Cenchrus ciliaris, and Baccharis neglecta. Infrequent vine. Corolla rose-purple.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Spur 454. Sample plot no. 47. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Thin, rocky (limestone) soils on bench above road; blackbrush shrubland with huisache, grassland croton, Texas persimmon, Lindheimer and Border pricklypears. With Acacia minuata, A. rigidula, Croton dioicus, Diospyros texana, Opuntia engelmannii var. lindheimeri, O. atrispina, and Aristida purpurea var. purpurea. Infrequent perennial to 30 cm. Rays and discs bright yellow.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Spur 454. Sample plot no. 47. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Rocky (limestone and asphalt), silty soil along roadside in former inundation zone; huisache-Roosevelt weed-salt cedar shrubland with silver bluestem. With Baccharis neglecta, Bothriochloa laguroides ssp. torreyana, and Acacia minuata. Infrequent tree to 5 m. Corolla white, inflorescence pendant.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Spur 454. Sample plot no. 47. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).

habitat: Thin, rocky (limestone) soils on bench above road; blackbrush shrubland with huisache, grassland croton, Texas persimmon, Lindheimer and Border pricklypears. With Acacia minuata, A. rigidula, Croton dioicus, Diospyros texana, Opuntia engelmannii var. lindheimeri, O. atrispina, Galium proliferum, and Aristida purpurea var. purpurea. Infrequent annual to 25 cm. Corolla bright deep purple.
locality: Amistad National Recreation Area: Spur 454. Sample plot no. 47. Del Rio NW Quad (1:24,000).
